{"title":"Polygon Bend mounts an affordable alloy gravel adventure bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/polygon-bend-mounts-an-affordable-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike/","date":1698161624000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1400\" height=\"905\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-1.jpg\" alt=\"polygon bend alloy gravel bike\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-1.jpg 1400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-1-297x192.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-1-800x517.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-1-120x78.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-1-768x496.jpg 768w\" /></p>\n<p>If you’re looking for a modern gravel bike that’s ready for adventures with all the mounts, 700×50 tire clearance, and dropper post compatibility, the new Polygon Bend is it. And it starts at just $1,499 for a complete bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1618\" height=\"488\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-4.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of mounting points on polygon bend alloy gravel bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-4.jpg 1618w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-4-297x90.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-4-800x241.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-4-120x36.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-4-768x232.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-4-1536x463.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Bend’s alloy frame starts with a sloping top tube that provides great standover clearance and keeps the weight low when it’s loaded down. And it’s easy to load, with hard mounting points for frame bags under the top tube, plus more mounts on the top side.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s also two bottle cages inside the front triangle and another underneath. The carbon fork adds three “anything cage” mounts plus rack and fender attachment points.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1618\" height=\"488\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of rack mounts on polygon bend alloy gravel bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike.jpg 1618w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-297x90.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-800x241.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-120x36.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-768x232.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-1536x463.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In the back are rack mounts for packing more. Those sit atop dropped seatstays, which bend and flatten to add a bit of compliance.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-5.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"729\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-5.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of head tube on polygon bend alloy gravel bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-5.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-5-297x180.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-5-800x486.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-5-120x73.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-5-768x467.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://bikesonline-usa.sjv.io/c/2227671/1307246/15955?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bikesonline.com%2Fpolygon-bend-r7-gravel-bike\">R7 model</a> shown above has SRAM Apex 1×11 mechanical for $1,499. Above that is is the Polygon Bend R9X with Rival AXS 1×12 with upgraded Novatec tubeless-ready wheels for $2,899 in Nautical Blue.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-V90X.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1400\" height=\"781\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-V90X.jpg\" alt=\"polygon bend V9X alloy gravel bike with suspension fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-V90X.jpg 1400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-V90X-297x166.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-V90X-800x446.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-V90X-120x67.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/polygon-bend-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike-V90X-768x428.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The top level <a href=\"https://bikesonline-usa.sjv.io/c/2227671/1307246/15955?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bikesonline.com%2Fpolygon-bend-v9x-gravel-bike\">Bend V9X </a>goes to SRAM GX AXS with Reverb XPLR AXS and a Fox AX32 suspension fork for $3,999.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.polygonbikes.com/bend-series/\" target=\"_blank\">PolygonBikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/polygon-bend-mounts-an-affordable-alloy-gravel-adventure-bike/\">Polygon Bend mounts an affordable alloy gravel adventure bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"2fc36442a21634f64b2b50eae4b9c932282e41474d6e1bd87772727e78d71bad","category":"Cycling"}